dp_152: Klebsiella pneumoniae is becoming a prevalent cause of neonatal sepsis and so far, there is not strategy to prevent vertical transmission from mother to babies during pregnancy. Further research is needed to understand the burden of this diseases in Ethiopia and address this issue such as vaccines development.   On the other hand, neural tube defect is very prevalent in Ethiopia, and spina bifida is the most common clinical presentation. It is well known that folate deficiency in pregnant women has a potential for impact on the prevalence of these neural tube defects and then to avoid them, adequate level of folic acid in mother's blood should be at the time of conception. However, Ethiopia is one of the few countries in Africa with no folic acid fortification. So, there is an urgency to implement effective programs to get all women of reproductive age to have adequate folic acid to prevent all of folic acid-preventable spina bifida and anencephaly, which would prevent 96% of spina bifida and anencephaly cases.
dpf_010: this death could be prevented with early identification of neural tube defect in ANC, in many cases, this neural tube defects are caused due to lack of folic acid in the mother. Once the mother is pregnant, if she does not have enough folic acid in their blood, the baby will not develop well his/her brain and this damage cannot be prevented. Most cases of spina bifida can be prevented if the mother gets enough folate before and during pregnancy.  Adding folic acid to flour has been found to be effective for most women or take ready to use folic acid pills. In order to treat a maternal infection avoiding the transmission to the baby in the next pregnancy, the mother should go to a health facility if she feels fever, vaginal discharge or some signs of urinary tract infection (burning feeling when you pee, a frequent or intense urge to pee, even though little comes out when you do, cloudy, dark, bloody, or strange-smelling urine, feeling tired or shaky, pain or pressure in your back or lower abdomen) to be treated as soon as possible and avoid the transmission to the baby.

dpf_010: Advise to the family:  Due to bad obstetric history of the mother, the general advice is always attending ANC as soon as the mother gets pregnant, and do a proper follow-up in the mother, with measuring sugar in blood and blood pressure. The mother is diabetic, and it is important with proper blood sugar control. In case of a next pregnancy, attending ANC as soon as possible after getting pregnant, doing a close follow-up of pregnancy. If there is any decreased in fetal movement, go to hospital immediately to check with ultrasound. At the time of labour, go soon to a hospital for delivery as they did in this case.   Advise for health facility/authorities: Promote close ANC follow-up of high risk mothers (as this one, with bad obstetric history). Improved resuscitation procedures, consider the use of surfactant and improve the use of CPAP. There is an urgent need of hospital acquired infection prevention and control, including and improved antibiotic use policy (avoid Cetriaxone in neonates). We strongly advice the health authorities to set up blood culture surveillance.

dpf_010: Advise to the caregiver: The mother attended ANC during pregnancy, and seeked help at the health centre when feeling abdominal pain, which is both very good. The general advice is always attending ANC as soon as the mother gets pregnant, and do a proper follow-up in the mother, with measuring sugar in blood and blood pressure. In case of a next pregnancy, attending ANC as soon as possible after getting pregnant, doing a close follow-up of pregnancy. If there is any decreased in fetal movement, go to hospital immediately to check with ultrasound. At the time of labour, go soon to a hospital for delivery as they did in this case.   Advise for health facility/authorities: Promote ANC follow-up. Improved resuscitation procedures, consider the use of surfactant and improve the use of CPAP and earlier use of oxygen. Death due infections in the baby can be prevented by improving health care management and with better resources in hospital, such as microbiology facilities (not available at Hiwot Fana).  Klebisella pneumonia was likely acquired in the hospital. This agent was resistant to the first and second line of antibiotic. Bacterial invasive diseases surveillance should be a must in referral hospitals for a better clinical management and infection and prevention control policy should be established and followed to prevent-reduce hospital acquired infections.      Advise for health authorities: There is an urgent need of hospital acquired infection prevention and control, including and improved antibiotic use policy. We strongly advice the health authorities to set up blood culture surveillance.

dpf_010: Advise to the caregiver:  In many cases, this kind of severe neural tube defect are caused due to lack of folic acid in the mother. Once the mother is pregnant, if she does not have enough folic acid in their blood, the baby will not develop well his/her brain and this damage cannot be prevented. The mother should take 5mg of folic acid daily (currently costs 1 ETB/tablet) from now up to end of reproductive age (increased risk of a second NTD).     Advise for health facility:  This severe neural tube defect could be detected very early during pregnancy and avoid the family early termination of pregnancy. This mother did not do any ANC. ANC attending is poor and more community engagement and awareness on institutional deliveries and ANC is needed to diagnosis early growth restriction and avoid complications associated to it.     Advise for health authorities: Neural tube defect is very prevalent in Ethiopia, and anencephaly is the most severe clinical presentation with fatal outcome. It is well known that folate deficiency in pregnant women has a potential for impact on the prevalence of these neural tube defects and then to avoid them, adequate level of folic acid in mother's blood should be at the time of conception. However, Ethiopia is one of the few countries in Africa with no folic acid fortification. So, there is an urgency to implement effective programs to get all women of reproductive age to have adequate folic acid to prevent all of folic acid-preventable spina bifida and anencephaly, which would prevent 96% of spina bifida and anencephaly cases.

dpf_010: •	Advise to the caregiver:  The family in this case did it fine including ANC (she should aim for next pregnancy to do at least 4 visits) and institutional delivery. The mother has a chronic cardiac illness, which we have little information about. But it will be important that her cardiac condition is controlled. We will advise the hospital how to improve health care management at the time of delivery as well as to take care of neonate.   Advise for health facility:  Birth asphyxia could be prevented with a proper health care management at delivery and a good referral system in case of adverse pregnancy outcome or difficult delivery. In this case it should have been considered to perform a C/S. Improvement in newborn health care is mandatory.   Advise for health authorities: Review of obstetric care management at delivery in health centres should be done as well as support to improve transport during referrals to hospitals from HCs.

dpf_010: Advise to the family: This mother did not do any ANC. Due to multiparity, this death could be prevented by having a good follow-up, earlier health seeking and better transportation to the hospital. In she gets pregnant again, she should not wait until have a spontaneous delivery and elective C-section should be done, as having a uterine rupture increases a lot the risk to have another uterine rupture and this is too risky for the fetus as well as for the mother (she can die due to acute anemia-bleeding). The best advice is family planning and avoid to have more kids.   Advise for health facility/health authorities: Improve community engagement activities to attend ANC, better documentation of ANC at HC levels and improve referral and transport system.

dp_157: CPL requested to review the case because histopathological findings of granulomas. CPL showed the granulomas in liver, lung and brain. Showed that the inflammation in the liver is composed by lymphocytes, histocytes and eosinophils. Discussed that ZNAF, GMS and MTB IHC was performed to rule out MTB and fungal infection and were negative; discussed that one of the differential diagnosis is parasitic infection (Schistosoma spp; Strongyloides stercoralis). Lola commented that parasitic infections are endemic in Ethiopia. CPL performed deep sections of tissues to look for parasites and eggs, but these were not identified. Discussed that TAC results were not provided and would be helpful in this case to detect possible MTB or other infections agents that results in granulomatous inflammation. IHC for Brucella spp. that was negative and will issue an addendum report with IHC results (still not available) and deep section looking for parasite negative

dp_152: Advice to the family:  this death could be prevented with early identification of neural tube defects in ANC, in many cases; these neural tube defects are caused due to lack of folic acid in the mother. Once the mother is pregnant, if she does not have enough vitamins in their blood, the baby will not develop well his/her brain and this damage cannot be prevented. Most neural tube defect cases including anencephaly can be prevented if the mother gets enough folate before and early stage of pregnancy.  Health-seeking behavior, saving money for delivery, good nutrition, and early initiation of ANC helps in preventing similar kinds of problems.  Advice for health facility:  this severe neural tube defect could be detected earlier in the pregnancy and advised the mother to do a closer follow-up. Spina bifida caused hydrocephalus, which made difficult the delivery. With better ANC care and early diagnosis of NTDs, a planned early termination of pregnancy to avoid intrauterine fetal distress could be done. Spina bifida can be corrected after birth and it does not necessarily cause death.   Advice for health authorities: neural tube defect is very prevalent in Ethiopia, and spina bifida is the most common clinical presentation. It is well known that folate deficiency in pregnant women has the potential to impact the prevalence of these neural tube defects and then to avoid them, an adequate level of folic acid in the mother's blood should be at the time of conception. However, Ethiopia is one of the few countries in Africa with no folic acid fortification. Therefore, there is an urgency to implement effective programs to get all women of reproductive age to have adequate folic acid to prevent all folic acid-preventable spina bifida and anencephaly, which would prevent the majority of spina bifida and anencephaly cases.

dp_152: •	Advise to the family:  This death could be prevented with early identification of neural tube defect in ANC, in many cases; these neural tube defects are caused due to lack of folic acid in the mother. Once the mother is pregnant, if she does not have enough folic acid in their blood, the baby will not develop well his/her brain and this damage cannot be prevented. Most cases of spina bifida can be prevented if the mother gets enough folate before and during pregnancy.    Advise for health facility:   pre-pregnancy folate supplementation and education on consuming folate rich food helps to prevent NTD. It is also defected early in the pregnancy and advice the mother to do a closer follow-up. Spina bifida caused hydrocephalus that made difficult the delivery.  Spina bifida can be corrected after birth and it does not necessarily cause death. IPC should be intensify in the hospital and appropriate clinical management of invasive bacterial diseases.  Advise for health authorities:, there is an urgency to implement effective programs to get all women of reproductive age to have adequate folic acid to prevent all of folic acid-preventable spina bifida and anencephaly, which would prevent majority of spina bifida and anencephaly cases.  The most effective one would be mandatory food fortification program.
